=== Anime ===
*''Dr. Slump – Arale-chan'' (TV anime, 1981–1986) – original concept, based on his manga ''Dr. Slump''
*''[[Crusher Joe]]'' (1983 film) – space station design
*''[[Dragon Ball (anime)|Dragon Ball]]'' (TV anime, 1986–1989) – original concept, based on of the first half of his manga ''Dragon Ball''
*{{nihongo|''Kosuke & Rikimaru: The Dragon of Konpei Island''|小助さま力丸さま -コンペイ島の竜-||original video animation, 1988}} – direction, script and character designs
*''[[Dragon Warrior: Legend of the Hero Abel|Dragon Quest]]'' (TV anime, 1989–1991) – original character designs
*''[[Dragon Ball Z]]'' (TV anime, 1989–1996) – original concept, based on of the second half of ''Dragon Ball''
*{{nihongo|''Pink: Water Bandit, Rain Bandit''|ＰＩＮＫ みずドロボウ あめドロボウ|Pinku Mizu Dorobō Ame Dorobō|1990 film}} – original concept, based on his one-shot manga ''Pink''
*{{nihongo|''Kennosuke-sama''|剣之介さま||1990 film}} – original concept, based on his one-shot manga of the same name
*''Go! Go! Ackman'' (1994 film) – original concept, based on his manga of the same name
*''[[Gulliver Boy|Imagination Science World Gulliver Boy]]'' (TV anime, 1995) – mechanical designs
*''[[Dragon Ball GT]]'' (TV anime, 1996–1997) – character designs, title and logo
*''Doctor Slump'' (TV anime, 1997–1999) – original concept, based on his manga ''Dr. Slump''
*''Blue Dragon'' (TV anime, 2007–2008) – character designs

=== Video game designs ===
*''Dragon Ball: Shenlong no Nazo'' (video game, 1986) – designed the {{nihongo|Kuririan|クリリアン}} character
*''[[Famicom Jump II: Saikyō no Shichinin]]'' (video game, 1991) – boss monster design
*''[[Dragon Quest]]'' series: a role-playing game (RPG) series published by [[Enix]] (now [[Square Enix]]).
*''[[Dragon Quest Monsters]]'' series: an RPG series published by Enix (now Square Enix).
*''[[Go! Go! Ackman]]'' adapted from the Go! Go! Ackman! manga.  Published by [[Banpresto]] 1994-1995, there are three Super Famicom action platformer games and one GameBoy game.
*''[[Chrono Trigger]]'': an RPG developed by [[Square (company)|Square]] (now Square Enix) for Nintendo's Super Famicom/Super NES. Toriyama appears in an alternate ending to the game along with all the other developers.
*''[[Tobal No. 1]]'' and ''[[Tobal 2]]'': Fighting games for Sony's PlayStation developed by Squaresoft (now Square Enix).
*''[[Blue Dragon]]'': an RPG for [[Microsoft]]'s [[Xbox 360]] developed by [[Artoon]] for [[Mistwalker]] studio based on a design by ''[[Final Fantasy]]'' originator [[Hironobu Sakaguchi]].
*''[[Blue Dragon: Awakened Shadow]]'': an RPG for Nintendo DS developed by Mistwalker and [[tri-Crescendo]] and published by [[Namco Bandai Games|Namco Bandai]] in Japan and [[D3 Publisher]] in North America and Europe. Toriyama also voices the character Toripo, which is modelled after his "Toribot" [[self-insertion|self-insert]].
*''[[Super Dragon Ball Z]]'' (video game, 2006, PS2 version): Fighting game developed by [[Arika]] based on his manga ''Dragon Ball''. He designed the {{nihongo|[[Frieza|Mecha Freeza]]|メカフリーザ}} character.
*''[[Dragon Ball Online]]'': a [[massively multiplayer online role-playing game]] based on ''Dragon Ball''.

